Description: Fragment of neck and sub-round handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine beige-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Teisagoras. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0214.33.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (274)
